text.tspan: Number of suicides per 100,000 people in a given population and year. Suicide deaths are underreported
in many countries due to social stigma and cultural or legal concerns. This data is adjusted for this
underreporting to estimate the actual rate of suicides.
Data source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019)
Note: To allow for comparisons between countries and over time, this metric is age-standardized.
